                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, March 30: The Reserve Bank of India has released the guidelines on how banks must classify capital in their balance sheets to ensure uniformity in reporting. The RBI has asked banks to classify perpetual non-cumulative preference shares as capital. Banks must adopt this classification while preparing their balance sheet for the current fiscal.                             
	 New Delhi, March 30: Hero Honda Motors board of directors considered and declared a Silver Jubilee Special Dividend of 4,000 per cent or Rs 80 per equity share of Rs 2 each. However, despite the bonanza, shares of the company declined 1.93 per cent to settle the day at Rs 1,966.70 on the Bombay Stock Exchange.                            
	 Dubai, March 30: The Dubai government today replaced the chairman of troubled real estate developer Nakheel and also appointed a new board as part of its efforts to recast and tackle its debt problems, a Financial Times report said.
                                                                                                                          
